		<title>04SAMSON AND THE DEVIL</title>
		<content> The Deil's Stane,Waltonhill           
                                       
 Samson challenged the devil to a rock 
 throwing contest. Samson stood on West
 Lomond Hill while the devil stood on  
 East Lomond Hill.                     
 The devil's rock landed on the        
 roadside 250m west of Waltonhill Farm 
 and still lies there.                 
 Samson was 300m further away but in   
 spite of that his throw went 250m     
 further than the devil's and split    
 into three pieces when it landed. The 
 three pieces were used in the building
 of the barn at Waltonhill.            
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
